description._content: Collection: Human Ecology Historical Photographs Title: Caption reads: ''Picnic of clubs near Ithaca, October 10, 1919. Cornell Study Clubs. Cayuga County Clubs meet at the College.'' Scene shows gathering on the deck of the home economics building (now Comstock Hall). Clubs included are East Genoa, Bolts Corners, Mecklenburg, Newfield, Inlet Valley, Brookton Ladies Aid, Slaterville Ladies Aid, Burdette, Ovid, Jordan, Minoa, and Baldwinsville. Collection #23-2-749, item PR-RC-03 Div. Rare & Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library Persistent URI: http://hdl.handle.net/1813.001/5w3q There are no known U.S. copyright restrictions on this image.
